message.content: The Sussex Spaniel is a breed of dog that originated in England. Its coat is typically golden liver in color, with a dense, silky texture. The breed has a sturdy, compact build with short, muscular legs and a wide, round head. The eyes are dark and round, with a friendly expression. The ears are long and hang close to the head. The breed is typically used as a hunting dog, but also makes a great family pet due to its gentle nature. Sussex Spaniels can be found in dog shows and in homes around the world.
